Title

Calculated Fields Used in Tableau

Content

A few calculated fields were created in Tableau to simplify analysis.

Example 1: Heart Disease Cases
COUNT([id])

Purpose:
To calculate the total number of patients.

Example 2: Average Cholesterol
AVG([chol])

Purpose:
To display the average cholesterol level.

Example 3: Average Blood Pressure
AVG([trestbps])

Purpose:
To analyze blood pressure trends.

Example 4 (Agar banaya ho): Age Group
IF [age] < 40 THEN "Young"
ELSEIF [age] < 60 THEN "Middle Age"
ELSE "Senior"
END

Purpose:
To classify patients into age groups.